wikipedia_page.main: Edmund Leach Chadwick (31 August 1847 – 6 August 1918) was an English cricketer active from 1875 to 1881 who played for Lancashire. He was born in Rochdale and died in Dorset. He appeared in 13 first-class matches as a righthanded batsman, scoring 254 runs with a highest score of 42, and held two catches.
